	<p>
	<h4><a name="content1_1">Why should I use Gidsy?</a></h4>
	We make it easy and hassle-free for you to organize any kind of activity or find something to do. Gidsy not only takes care of all the stuff you shouldn't have to worry about, but we also add some extra benefits on top! 
	Gidsy will help you in different ways:  
	Convenience - Manage your activities and bookings, receipts, custom requests, cancellations and many other things, all in one place. 
	Security & Protection - Using our highly secure payment system, we can guarantee safe online money transactions between organizers and participants. 
	Support - Need a hand? We provide speedy customer service for you and your participants, around the clock. 
	Engage & Expand - Reach a growing community of tourists and locals, connect with your audience, and build a trusted reputation by receiving reviews and recommendations.

	
	
	<p>
	<h4><a name="content1_2">Who can organize something on Gidsy?</a></h4>
	Anyone can organize an activity on Gidsy. If your activity answers the question “What to do?”, Gidsy is definitely the place for you. Whether you’re a crafter who wants to share your DIY passion, an aspiring top chef who wants to start a food revolution or a beekeeper offering tours of your urban apiary - your activities are welcome on Gidsy! 
	While we try to be as welcoming as possible, there are a few things that are not allowed on Gidsy.
	Learn more about using Gidsy as a small business or group of people in the FAQ 'Can I have an account for my company or a group of people?'.

	
	<p>
	<h4><a name="content1_3">What are the costs to create a listing?</a></h4>
	Listing an activity on Gidsy is free of charge. We charge a 10% service fee when a booking has been done. For example, if you have listed an activity for $50 per person, you will receive $45 for every successful booking that happens through Gidsy. 
	Learn more about our 10% service fee in the FAQ 'How does Gidsy make money?'


	<p>
	<h4><a name="content1_4">Where can I use Gidsy?</a></h4>
	Gidsy is internationally focused. Anyone, anywhere can organize and book activities on Gidsy.
	If you are looking for something to do in your area, this is because no one has organized any activities yet! Be the first, and create a listing on Gidsy, or get in touch with us about how you can kickstart Gidsy in your area.
	
	<p>
	<h4><a name="content1_5">What's not allowed on Gidsy?</a></h4>
	While we try to be as welcoming as possible, Gidsy is not suited for:
	Renting out apartments, rooms or accommodations. There are other websites out there that do a much better job at that.
	Illegal activities, or activities that involve or imply sexual acts.
	Things that could be offensive to others. Keep in mind, and please respect that we’re a community of many different cultures, and want everyone to feel comfortable and included.
	Please bear in mind that you’re always responsible for what happens at your own event, so safety first!
	
	<p>
	<h4><a name="content2_1">How do I create a listing on Gidsy?</a></h4>
	Login, or create an account on Gidsy.
	Then, go to the ‘Organize an activity’ button on the top.
	You are now ready to create a listing. Provide all the information that's needed and you're done.
	Now, request approval of the listing and we will get back to you as soon as possible.
	If you run into any trouble, don't hesitate to send us an email at support@gidsy.com.
	
	<p>
	<h4><a name="content2_2">How long does it take for Gidsy to approve my listing after requesting an activation?</a></h4>
	How long does it take for Gidsy to approve my listing after requesting an activation?
	This all depends on the listing, but we will respond to your activation request within 48 hours. If you have any questions, you can always contact us via support@gidsy.com.
